### 1. üöÄ Core Curriculum (Circle 1)
*The main engineering track. These projects focus on building robust, reusable libraries and understanding system-level I/O.*

| Project | Description & Key Concepts | Status |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
circle 0
| **Libft** | **The Standard Library:** My first C library. I reimplemented 40+ standard C functions (e.g., `memset`, `strlcat`, `calloc`) and custom linked-list manipulation tools. This library serves as the foundation for all future C projects. | ‚úÖ Done |
Circle 1
| **ft_printf** | **Variadic Functions:** A mimic of the standard `printf`. Handles variable argument lists (`va_list`) and parses format specifiers (`cspdiuxX%`) to manage standard output directly. | ‚úÖ Done |
| **get_next_line**| **Static Variables & File Descriptors:** Reading a line from a file descriptor efficiently, managing buffers and memory leaks across multiple function calls. | üöß Next Up |
